Senator DORGAN. Ms. Williams, I didn’t quite understand, is Hal-
liburton still doing business, but has announced that it will not do 
business  in  the  future  beyond  this  contract,  or  are  all  of  your  con-
tracts now completed and you are no longer doing business through 
a foreign subsidiary in the country of Iran? 

Ms.  WILLIAMS.  All  of  our  contracts  are  completed  and  we  no 
longer have any further operations. There are some wind-down pro-
cedures  that  are  happening,  but  that  is  not  active  operational 
work. 

Senator  DORGAN.  In  2005,  Mr.  Lesar,  the  CEO,  said  that  when 
he  announced  that  Halliburton  would  no  longer  do  business  in 
Iran, ‘‘if more of our customers go there, we will return to this mar-
ket.’’ Has that changed? 

